Valve’s Steam Link will soon get dedicated apps for iOS and Android devices, SlashGear reported. Steam Link allows users to stream gameplay from their PC and play on supported devices with minimal latency. The new apps will add support for smartphones and tablets which support high-bandwidth 5GHz Wi-Fi connections. Valve’s Steam Controller will also be supported by the new Steam Link App. The report stated that the Steam Link apps would be available the week of 21 May 2018.